{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846425718,"sessionID":"ses_287510ae9ffeOG04UnYpli5Vao","part":{"id":"prt_d78af0e60001WldboA6gnfwP2I","messageID":"msg_d78af0417001K72CKsvr0Xufko","sessionID":"ses_287510ae9ffeOG04UnYpli5Vao","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_3489c9670ddc4a55af2521f1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project layout - what directories exist at the root level\n2. The pkg/agentd directory structure and existing code patterns\n3. Any existing design.md files or design document patterns in the project\n4. How other controllers or similar components are structured in pkg/\n5. Any existing idle cleanup or garbage collection related code\n6. The Go module name and dependencies (go.mod)\n7. Any existing configuration patterns for agentd\n\nSearch in the workspace root: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z\n\nReturn detailed findings about the project structure, existing patterns, and any relevant code that would inform the design of an \"Agentd 空闲清理控制器\" (Idle Cleanup Controller).","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28750db89ffeKbCm3puxCbtiVK (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is my detailed report:\n\n---\n\n## AgentCube Project Structure Exploration -- Complete Findings\n\n### 1. Overall Project Layout (Root Level)\n\nThe project root at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z` contains:\n\n| Directory/File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/` | Binary entry points (currently only `cmd/picod/`) |\n| `pkg/` | Go packages (6 subdirectories) |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes client code (clientset, informers, listers) |\n| `changes/` | 18 change requests (AR-001 through AR-018), each with design.md, proposal.md, etc. |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | **Design spec for idle cleanup** (design.md, spec.md) |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration design and spec |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing design and spec |\n| `session-store/` | Session store design and spec |\n| `code-execution/` | Code execution design and spec |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI toolkit design and spec |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK design and spec |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment design and spec |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design and spec |\n| `integrations/` | Integrations design and spec |\n| `testing/` | Test manifest |\n| `go.mod` / `go.sum` | Go module definition |\n| `design.md` | Root design document (currently AR-016: PicoD File Management) |\n| `project.md` | Project context overview |\n| `proposal.md` | Root proposal |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Root delta spec |\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `pkg/` Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/\n├── apis/\n│   └── runtime/\n│       └── v1alpha1/          -- CRD types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter), groupversion info, constants\n├── common/\n│   └── types/\n│       └── types.go           -- Kind constants (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Sandbox, SandboxClaim)\n├── picod/\n│   ├── server.go              -- Gin HTTP server\n│   ├── config.go              -- CLI flag parsing\n│   ├── auth.go                -- JWT auth manager\n│   ├── execute.go             -- Code execution handler\n│   ├── files.go               -- Legacy file handlers\n│   ├── files/                 -- File management subpackage (AR-016)\n│   └── types.go               -- Request/Response types\n├── router/\n│   ├── server.go, config.go   -- Router HTTP server and config\n│   ├── proxy.go, backend.go   -- Proxy and backend logic\n│   ├── session_manager.go     -- Session management\n│   ├── loadbalancer.go        -- Load balancing\n│   ├── middleware.go, jwt.go  -- Auth middleware\n│   └── informer.go, health.go -- K8s informer, health checks\n├── store/\n│   ├── store.go               -- Store interface\n│   ├── store_redis.go         -- Redis implementation\n│   ├── store_valkey.go        -- Valkey implementation\n│   └── codec.go, singleton.go -- Encoding and singleton patterns\n└── workloadmanager/\n    ├── handler/               -- Sandbox CRUD, lifecycle management\n    ├── reconciler/            -- SandboxReconciler (custom informer-based, NOT controller-runtime)\n    ├── middleware/            -- (empty)\n    └── response/              -- HTTP response helpers\n```\n\n**Key observation:** There is NO `pkg/agentd/` directory yet. AR-018 is the change request to create it.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Go Module and Dependencies\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go version:** 1.25.0\n\nKey dependencies:\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.22.2` -- Already available for use\n- `k8s.io/api v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1`, `k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1`\n- `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` -- Sandbox CRD types (from `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`)\n- `github.com/gin-gonic/gin v1.10.0` -- HTTP framework\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.18.0`, `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go v1.0.73`\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.22.0` -- Metrics\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Design Document Patterns\n\nThe project follows a structured design pattern with files in `changes/AR-XXX/`:\n- `proposal.md` -- Purpose, scope, architecture, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `design.md` -- Detailed technical implementation (architecture, data structures, API contracts, core implementation, testing)\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Gherkin-style requirements with scenarios\n- `tasks.md` -- Implementation task checklist\n\nThe root `design.md` follows a 9-section template:\n1. Architecture (Purpose, Package Layout, Data Flow, Dependencies)\n2. Data Structures (Config, Interfaces, Request/Response types, Constants, Sentinel Errors)\n3. API Contracts (Route Table, per-endpoint specs, Error Response Format)\n4. Core Implementation (Constructor, key algorithms, route registration)\n5. Error Handling\n6. Testing Strategy (Unit test matrix, test helpers, mock strategy, gate requirements)\n7. Deployment Considerations\n8. Implementation Steps (phased plan)\n9. Future Changes\n\n---\n\n### 5. AR-018: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller (Current State)\n\n**AR-018** is the active change request for the \"Agentd 空闲清理控制器\" (Idle Cleanup Controller).\n\n**Current status:**\n- `proposal.md` -- Complete and detailed\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Complete with full Gherkin scenarios\n- `design.md` -- **Stub only** (all sections are `<!-- TODO -->`)\n- `tasks.md` -- Stub (only placeholder task)\n\n**Key specifications from delta-spec.md:**\n\n```\nPackage layout:\ncmd/agentd/\n└── main.go              -- Binary entry point\npkg/agentd/\n├── reconciler.go        -- Reconciler struct, Reconcile, SetupWithManager\n├── reconciler_test.go   -- Unit tests\n└── const.go             -- SessionExpirationTimeout constant\n```\n\n**Core algorithm (exactly specified):**\n1. `Get` Sandbox by `req.NamespacedName`\n2. If `NotFound` --> `return (Result{}, nil)`\n3. If other error --> `return (Result{}, err)`\n4. Read annotation `last-activity-time` from `sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`\n5. If missing or empty --> `return (Result{}, nil)`\n6. Parse as RFC3339; if error --> `return (Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n7. `expirationTime = lastActivity + SessionExpirationTimeout`\n8. If `now.After(expirationTime)`: Delete sandbox; handle NotFound as success\n9. Else: `return (Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil)`\n\n**Key constants:**\n- `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` (needs to be defined in `pkg/workloadmanager`)\n\n**Sandbox CRD:** `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, kind `Sandbox`, from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Idle Cleanup / Garbage Collection Code\n\nThere are **two** existing cleanup mechanisms:\n\n#### A. WorkloadManager LifecycleManager (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go`)\n- Polling-based GC cycle (default 5-minute interval)\n- Four cleanup sub-tasks:\n  - `cleanupExpiredSandboxes` -- TTL-based and idle-based cleanup via Redis Store\n  - `cleanupOrphanCRs` -- Finds CRs with no corresponding Store entry\n  - `cleanupGhostEntries` -- Finds Store entries with no corresponding CR\n- Uses `DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- Annotation key: `AnnotationIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n- Cleanup reasons: `ttl_expired`, `idle`, `orphan_cr`, `ghost_entry`\n\n#### B. WorkloadManager SandboxReconciler (`pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`)\n- Custom informer-based reconciler (NOT controller-runtime pattern)\n- Uses workqueue with exponential backoff\n- Watches AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and Pod resources\n- Syncs Pod IP changes to Store\n\n#### C. idle-cleanup/design.md (Legacy reference design)\n- Located at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/design.md`\n- Describes the same algorithm as AR-018 but as a reference document\n- References `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Existing Controller/Reconciler Patterns\n\n#### WorkloadManager Reconciler Pattern (`pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`)\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    clientset       clientset.Interface\n    informerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    arLister        listers.AgentRuntimeLister\n    ciLister        listers.CodeInterpreterLister\n    podInformer     coreinformers.PodInformer\n    store           Store\n    workqueue       workqueue.RateLimitingInterface\n    workers         int\n    metricsRecorder handler.MetricsRecorder\n    mu              sync.Mutex\n    running         bool\n    stopCh          chan struct{}\n}\n```\n- Uses `cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs` for Add/Update/Delete\n- `Run(stopCh)` starts informers, waits for cache sync, spawns workers\n- `syncHandler(key)` dispatches to specific reconcile methods\n\n#### Sandbox Orchestration Reconciler Pattern (from sandbox-orchestration/design.md)\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n    watchers map[types.NamespacedName]chan SandboxStatusUpdate\n    mu       sync.RWMutex\n}\n```\n- This IS the controller-runtime pattern (embeds `client.Client`)\n- Used for watching Sandbox status changes\n\n---\n\n### 8. Configuration Patterns\n\n**PicoD (`pkg/picod/config.go`):**\n- Simple struct with JSON tags\n- `ParseFlags()` using `flag.NewFlagSet`\n- Environment variable fallback (e.g., `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`)\n\n**Router (`pkg/router/config.go`):**\n- `NewDefaultConfig()` returns sensible defaults\n- Duration-based config fields (`SessionCheckInterval`, `SessionIdleTimeout`, etc.)\n\n**WorkloadManager LifecycleManager:**\n- Dependency injection via `LifecycleManagerDeps` struct\n- Zero-value defaults applied in constructor\n\n---\n\n### 9. Important Finding: Missing Constant\n\nThe `LastActivityAnnotationKey` constant is referenced throughout the AR-018 specs as `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` with value `\"last-activity-time\"`, but **it does NOT currently exist in `pkg/workloadmanager/`**. It exists in:\n- `pkg/router/config.go` as `\"agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity\"` (different value!)\n- `sandbox-orchestration/design.md` as `\"last-activity-time\"` (design doc only)\n\nThis constant needs to be added to `pkg/workloadmanager` as part of AR-018 implementation.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Summary of Key Files for AR-018 Implementation\n\n| File | Path | Status |\n|---|---|---|\n| AR-018 Proposal | `changes/AR-018/proposal.md` | Complete |\n| AR-018 Delta Spec | `changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md` | Complete |\n| AR-018 Design | `changes/AR-018/design.md` | **STUB (needs filling)** |\n| AR-018 Tasks | `changes/AR-018/tasks.md` | **STUB** |\n| Idle Cleanup Spec | `idle-cleanup/spec.md` | Complete reference |\n| Idle Cleanup Design | `idle-cleanup/design.md` | Complete reference |\n| LifecycleManager | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go` | Existing GC code |\n| Handler Constants | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go` | Has `DefaultIdleTimeout`, `AnnotationIdleTimeout` |\n| Sandbox GVR | `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/constants.go` | `SandboxGVR = agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes` |\n| Common Types | `pkg/common/types/types.go` | Has `SandboxKind = \"Sandbox\"` |\n| Picod main.go | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Pattern for binary entry point |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28750db89ffeKbCm3puxCbtiVK","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775846237299,"end":1775846425715}}}}
